In his weekly message, the President spoke from the Nuclear Security Summit about the threat of terrorists acquiring nuclear weapons. He highlighted efforts to secure nuclear materials and emphasized the collaboration with other nations in eliminating or safeguarding enough material for over 150 nuclear weapons. The President reiterated the commitment to destroying ISIL and discussed ways to increase efforts to prevent terrorist attacks. He also mentioned that progress has been made at the summit in securing nuclear materials and vowed to continue working to keep the nation safe.